Brave Asset Management Inc. Cuts Stake in Gilead Sciences, Inc. (GILD)

					Posted by Francis Steltz on Jul 17th, 2017 // No Comments 



Brave Asset Management Inc. cut its position in  Gilead Sciences, Inc. (NASDAQ:GILD) by 8.3% during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor  owned 30,621 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock after selling 2,778 shares during the period. Gilead Sciences accounts for approximately  1.2% of Brave Asset Management Inc.’s holdings, making the stock its 24th largest position. Brave Asset Management Inc.’s holdings in Gilead Sciences were worth $2,080,000 at the end of the most recent reporting period. 
Other hedge funds have also recently made changes to their positions in the company. Hall Laurie J Trustee increased its stake in shares of  Gilead Sciences by 20.0% in the first quarter. Hall Laurie J Trustee now owns 1,500 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock worth $100,000 after buying an additional 250 shares in the last quarter.  Cable Hill Partners LLC increased its stake in shares of  Gilead Sciences by 51.9% in the first quarter. Cable Hill Partners LLC now owns 1,584 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock worth $107,000 after buying an additional 541 shares in the last quarter.  Dubuque Bank & Trust Co. increased its stake in shares of  Gilead Sciences by 19.4% in the first quarter. Dubuque Bank & Trust Co. now owns 1,642 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock worth $112,000 after buying an additional 267 shares in the last quarter.  Webster Bank N. A. increased its stake in shares of  Gilead Sciences by 51.7% in the first quarter. Webster Bank N. A. now owns 1,831 shares of the biopharmaceutical company’s stock worth $125,000 after buying an additional 624 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Thomas J. Herzfeld Advisors Inc. purchased a new stake in shares of  Gilead Sciences during the fourth quarter worth approximately $143,000. Institutional investors own  74.03% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Gilead Sciences Inc. alerts:



Shares of Gilead Sciences, Inc. (GILD) opened at 70.57 on Monday. The firm has a market capitalization of $92.22 billion, a PE ratio of 7.46 and a beta of 1.20. The company’s 50 day moving average price is $66.03 and its 200-day moving average price is $68.95. Gilead Sciences, Inc. has a 52 week low of $63.76 and a 52 week high of $88.85. 




Gilead Sciences (NASDAQ:GILD) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, May 2nd. The biopharmaceutical company reported $2.20 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $2.18 by $0.02. The business had revenue of $6.51 billion during the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $6.66 billion. Gilead Sciences had a return on equity of 76.64% and a net margin of 43.42%.  On average, equities research analysts expect that  Gilead Sciences, Inc. will post $8.37 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
The firm also recently declared a quarterly dividend, which was paid on Thursday, June 29th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 16th were issued a dividend of $0.52 per share. The ex-dividend date of this dividend  was Wednesday, June 14th. This represents a $2.08 dividend on an annualized basis and a yield of 2.95%. Gilead Sciences’s payout ratio is currently 21.99%. 
